The paper deals with the problem of cross-modal matching between neuromorphic events and color images, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The proposed method involves adversarial learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also contributes to the development of a new dataset, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
